Never used Google Ads, but you should be able to do something like<p><pre><code>  var GoogleAd = React.createClass({
    getInitialState: function() {
      return {
        id: makeUniqueId()
      };
    },
    render: function() {
      // Since this is always the same, React won&#x27;t try to change the contents
      return <div id={this.state.id} />;
    },
    componentDidMount: function() {
      googletag.defineSlot(&#x27;/1234567/sports&#x27;, [728, 90], this.state.id);
    },
    componentWillUnmount: function() {
      // Clean up the slot and any other resources here
    }
  });
</code></pre>
and then not worry about it.

the String function is also a nice way to cast a value to a string (using .toString() is unsafe because it may not exist, such as with undefined and null): String(42) === &quot;42&quot;.<p>An other thing that could maybe be covered is this specifity:<p><pre><code>    typeof &quot;42&quot; === &quot;string&quot;
    typeof String(42) === &quot;string&quot;
    typeof new String(42) === &quot;object&quot;
</code></pre>
Native constructors are ... fun beasts, to say the least.
